                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 12.944,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 80499,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Court in 78-1155, of Vitek, Correctional Director against Jones will be announced by Mr. Justice White."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 12.944,
                        "stop": 125.129,
                        "byte_start": 80499,
                        "byte_stop": 529283,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15071,
                            "name": "Byron R. White",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/byron_r_white",
                            "last_name": "White",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2715,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -243367200,
                                    "date_end": 741243600,
                                    "appointing_president": "John F. Kennedy",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2715"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32699,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 55559,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/byron_r_white.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 11396,
                            "identifier": "byron_r_white"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 12.944,
                                "stop": 19.603,
                                "byte_start": 80499,
                                "byte_stop": 107144,
                                "text": "This case is here on appeal from a three-judge District Court with the District of Nebraska."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.603,
                                "stop": 34.505,
                                "byte_start": 107144,
                                "byte_stop": 166703,
                                "text": "The question is whether a state prisoner is entitled to a hearing when he is declared to be suffering from a mental disease or defect and transferred to a mental hospital for a treatment that is not available in the prison."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.505,
                                "stop": 52.38,
                                "byte_start": 166703,
                                "byte_stop": 238279,
                                "text": "The three-judge court held that the Due Process Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment requires a hearing and specified the procedures to be included in -- in the hearing including a holding that counsel was required."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.38,
                                "stop": 60,
                                "byte_start": 238279,
                                "byte_stop": 268685,
                                "text": "Because of the question of mootness, we postponed the -- the question of jurisdiction to the merits and heard oral argument."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60,
                                "stop": 68.185,
                                "byte_start": 268685,
                                "byte_stop": 301495,
                                "text": "As indicated in an opinion on file with the clerk, a majority of five justices holds that the case is not moot."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.185,
                                "stop": 87.804,
                                "byte_start": 301495,
                                "byte_stop": 379967,
                                "text": "We then agree with the district court that under the Due Process Clause, a prisoner about to be transferred to a mental hospital is entitled to notice and a hearing, to be present, offer testimony and cross-examined, and they\u0027ll have an independent maker and a written statement of the evidence and the reasons for the transfer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.804,
                                "stop": 96.099,
                                "byte_start": 379967,
                                "byte_stop": 413090,
                                "text": "Four of us, Justices Brennan, Marshall, Stevens, and I, also agree with the District Court that the prisoner is entitled with the help of counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.099,
                                "stop": 107.022,
                                "byte_start": 413090,
                                "byte_stop": 456767,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Powell, however, has indicated in his separate opinion concurring in part would require a competent help for the prisoner but not necessarily a licensed attorney."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.022,
                                "stop": 113.789,
                                "byte_start": 456767,
                                "byte_stop": 483830,
                                "text": "The judgment of the District Court is accordingly modified in this respect and is modified that it is affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.789,
                                "stop": 120.322,
                                "byte_start": 483830,
                                "byte_stop": 510056,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stewart and Mr. Justice Blackmun have filed dissenting opinions on the jurisdictional aspect of the case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.322,
                                "stop": 125.129,
                                "byte_start": 510056,
                                "byte_stop": 529283,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice and Mr. Justice Rehnquist have joined Mr. Justice Stewart."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
